A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO FIRE PREVENTION.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 132, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended by adding two new sections to be appropriately
3 designated and to read as follows:
4 "§132- State fire code; county amendments; minimum
5 standards. (a) The state fire code adopted pursuant to section
6 132-3 shall constitute the minimum statewide standard for fire
7 and life safety.
8 (b) No county shall adopt, amend, or enforce any
9 ordinance, rule, or code provision that is less restrictive than
10 the state fire code.
11 (c) A county may propose amendments to the state fire code
12 only where the amendments are equally or more restrictive than
13 the state fire code and are necessary to address unique local
14 conditions.
15 (d) All amendments proposed by a county shall be submitted
16 to the office of the state fire marshal for review and approval
17 before adoption or enforcement.
