1 (e) The office of the state fire marshal shall review
2 proposed amendments for consistency with statewide fire and life
3 safety objectives, statutory authority, and nationally
4 recognized standards, and shall approve, approve with
5 conditions, or deny the proposed amendments in writing.
6 (f) Nothing in this section shall be construed to limit
7 the authority of the office of the state fire marshal to provide
8 technical assistance, guidance, or model amendments to counties.
9 §132- State fire and life safety special fund. (a)
10 There is established in the state treasury the state fire and
11 life safety special fund, which shall be administered by the
12 office of the state fire marshal.
13 (b) The following shall be deposited into the special
14 fund:
15 (1) Federal, state, county, and private grants;
16 (2) Gifts, donations, bequests, and contributions from
17 public or private sources;
18 (3) Rebates, reimbursements, settlements, or cost
19 recoveries related to fire and life safety activities;
20 (4) Any interest earned or accrued on the moneys in the
21 special fund; and
