1 (e) Moneys in the special fund shall not lapse to the
2 general fund at the end of any fiscal year.
3 (f) The state fire marshal shall include information on
4 deposits to and expenditures from the special fund in the office
5 of the state fire marshal's annual report or other reports
6 required by law."
7 SECTION 2. Section 132-6, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
8 amended by amending subsections (a) and (b) to read as follows:
9 "(a) Each county fire chief, in person or by officers or
10 members of the fire chief's fire department designated by the
11 fire chief for that purpose, shall inspect all buildings[—] a^
12 premises, [and public thoroughfares,] except the interiors of
13 private dwellings and state facilities, for the purpose of
14 ascertaining and causing to be corrected any conditions liable
15 to cause fire or any violation of any law, ordinance, rule, or
16 order relating to fire hazard or to the prevention of fires.
17 (b) The inspection shall be made at least once every five
18 years, or as often as deemed practicable or necessary by the
19 county fire chief, at all other buildings and premises to
20 provide fire prevention and pre-fire planning within the
21 jurisdiction of the county fire chief. The office of the state
